r scientific results that help shape successful policies to improve the educational experience of young chinese rural students conduct real world experiment based research investigating how targeted policy assistance such as scholarships new ways of teaching and other new educational initiatives can open new opportunities for primary and secondary school students to achieve more and higher quality education we work with collaborators in china government officials international organizations ngos corporate and individual donors and others to evaluate programs and disseminate the results of our research read a summary of reaps key policy impacts to date stanford university all rights reserved 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints rss+ rss xml feeds
